This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it proposes a novel objective for multi-goal reinforcement learning and evaluates it on a set of robotic tasks. It also involves the use of Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient, which is a popular algorithm in the field of deep reinforcement learning. Additionally, the paper involves the use of entropy regularization, which is a common technique in machine learning for encouraging exploration and diversity. Other likely categories include Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), as the paper involves the use of reinforcement learning for robotic tasks and may involve visual inputs.
